Project: Landing Page Clone - UsabilityHub
This project is a responsive landing page clone built using HTML and CSS. It replicates the layout and design of the UsabilityHub website to help me practice modern front-end web development skills.

Features-
Top banner for announcements
Navigation bar with logo and links
Hero section with call-to-action
Trusted companies showcase
Features section with icons and descriptions
Visual cards highlighting use cases
Example section with different user scenarios
Call-to-action section to engage users
Footer with helpful links
Fully responsive design using Flexbox and media queries

Tech Stack-
HTML5
CSS3
Font Awesome (for icons)

Purpose-
This project was created as part of my beginner web development journey to strengthen my understanding of HTML structure, CSS styling, layout techniques, and responsive design.
What I Learned-
Writing semantic and structured HTML
Styling components with reusable CSS classes
Using Flexbox for layout and alignment
Creating responsive layouts for different screen sizes
Organizing a complete multi-section web page
